1
00:00:00,680 --> 00:00:05,589
Hello guys, in this video i will reveal an
effective trading strategy involving the commodity

2
00:00:05,589 --> 00:00:10,200
channel index, strategy which i mainly used
when I’m trading stocks.

3
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:15,280
The CCI is an oscillator used in technical
analysis in order to measure the variation

4
00:00:15,280 --> 00:00:18,410
of a stock’s price from its statistical
mean.

5
00:00:18,410 --> 00:00:24,510
High values indicate that prices are unusually
high compared to average prices.

6
00:00:24,510 --> 00:00:28,830
Low values of the CCI indicate that prices
are unusually low.

7
00:00:28,830 --> 00:00:33,690
CCI is one of the most popular indicators
and traders always tweak the settings of the

8
00:00:33,690 --> 00:00:38,440
indicator, depending on their favorite time
frame or trading style.

9
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:44,080
Most of them use the standard settings, CCI
set on a 21 period.

10
00:00:44,080 --> 00:00:49,370
CCI of 14-period and 50-period are also popular
among traders.

11
00:00:49,370 --> 00:00:53,649
Our CCI trading strategy involves 3 conditions
to be met.

12
00:00:53,649 --> 00:01:00,780
Here’s the first condition: the CCI must
reach overbought or oversold conditions twice.

13
00:01:00,780 --> 00:01:05,000
Commodity channel index is used by many people
in a wrong way.

14
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:12,210
When the CCI technical indicator hits or exceeds
values above -100 or 100, many traders interpret

15
00:01:12,210 --> 00:01:18,270
this as a signal to enter counter trend positions,
in response to overbought and oversold conditions

16
00:01:18,270 --> 00:01:19,380
on the market.

17
00:01:19,380 --> 00:01:24,290
But sometimes the prices can stay a long time
in the overbought or oversold areas and during

18
00:01:24,290 --> 00:01:27,130
that time they can continue to go higher or
lower.

19
00:01:27,130 --> 00:01:32,920
That’s why we need the CCI to reach overbought
or oversold conditions twice.

20
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:41,460
Also, we will use values of 200 and -200 for
these levels, to eliminate most of the noise.

21
00:01:41,460 --> 00:01:49,180
In this NVidia chart, observe the CCI reaching
oversold conditions twice, respectively -200

22
00:01:49,180 --> 00:01:50,190
level.

23
00:01:50,190 --> 00:01:55,070
Here’s the same condition met on an exon
mobile chart.

24
00:01:55,070 --> 00:02:01,939
The CCI reached -200 level once, and another
time 2 weeks after.

25
00:02:01,939 --> 00:02:07,640
Most people would have taken a long signal
the first time the CCI reached oversold conditions,

26
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:10,969
but this is a sure way to lose money on the
long run.

27
00:02:10,969 --> 00:02:18,239
It’s better to be conservative and wait
for the second move in oversold territory.

28
00:02:18,239 --> 00:02:19,650
But this isn’t enough.

29
00:02:19,650 --> 00:02:22,640
We need something else to happen on our charts.

30
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:24,719
Here’s our second condition.

31
00:02:24,719 --> 00:02:28,319
We need a regular divergence between the CCI
and the price.

32
00:02:28,319 --> 00:02:34,599
A regular divergence is characterized by higher
high prices and lower CCI indicator values

33
00:02:34,599 --> 00:02:41,930
during an uptrend and lower low prices plus
by higher CCI values, during a downtrend.

34
00:02:41,930 --> 00:02:47,319
Most novice traders search for CCI divergences
on the charts and automatically interpret

35
00:02:47,319 --> 00:02:50,709
this as a valid signal to enter the market.

36
00:02:50,709 --> 00:02:55,760
Just because a CCI divergence appears on a
chart, that doesn’t mean that you should

37
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:58,519
automatically enter a reverse position.

38
00:02:58,519 --> 00:03:07,969
So, we need the CCI to reach -200 or 200 level,
but it also has to form a divergence.

39
00:03:07,969 --> 00:03:14,760
In this Verizon Communication chart, we spot
a regular divergence on the CCI, but we also

40
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:21,790
take into account the first condition, respectively
the indicator must reach the -200 level.

41
00:03:21,790 --> 00:03:27,409
Here’s the same 2 conditions met on an AT&T
chart.

42
00:03:27,409 --> 00:03:35,559
The CCI reached the -200 level and formed
a regular divergence.

43
00:03:35,559 --> 00:03:41,499
By now, I’m sure you noticed that i only
showed examples with the CCI in oversold conditions

44
00:03:41,499 --> 00:03:45,079
and none of the examples were on the overbought
side.

45
00:03:45,079 --> 00:03:50,349
This is because when I’m trading stocks
I’m comfortable to trade only long positions,

46
00:03:50,349 --> 00:03:56,199
on stocks with good fundamentals (mainly dividend
stocks or growth stocks), so i intentionally

47
00:03:56,199 --> 00:03:58,750
look only for long signals.

48
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:03,430
To increase your chances when trading this
strategy, it’s good to have fundamentals

49
00:04:03,430 --> 00:04:04,579
on your side.

50
00:04:04,579 --> 00:04:09,170
I use a stock screener to keep an eye on the
stocks to trade.

51
00:04:09,170 --> 00:04:13,890
Stock screeners make a trader’s life a lot
simpler than the old days.

52
00:04:13,890 --> 00:04:19,209
You still have to do your homework, but you
can set screens to create your watch list

53
00:04:19,209 --> 00:04:23,669
based on your conditions and it’s going
to save you a lot of time, especially if you’re

54
00:04:23,669 --> 00:04:26,680
monitoring hundreds or thousands of stocks.

55
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:29,349
With a stock screener, you have a big advantage.

56
00:04:29,349 --> 00:04:34,720
I’ve put several stock screeners in the
description, if you want both technical and

57
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:39,590
fundamental indicators on your side with this
strategy, check them out.

58
00:04:39,590 --> 00:04:47,689
Like i said before, you could take signals
when the CCI reaches overbought conditions,

59
00:04:47,689 --> 00:04:53,720
like this one on the Netflix chart, but from
my experience, the most profitable trades

60
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:57,550
are buy entries on stocks with good fundamentals.

61
00:04:57,550 --> 00:05:02,780
This trade for example, would have brought
some profits eventually, but not without a

62
00:05:02,780 --> 00:05:04,509
period of consolidation.

63
00:05:04,509 --> 00:05:12,650
So, take my advice and look only on the lower
side of the CCI and ignore overbought signals.

64
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:18,810
Now, for the third conditions, we want to
see a clear trend line break in order to enter

65
00:05:18,810 --> 00:05:20,370
the market.

66
00:05:20,370 --> 00:05:26,450
We want to see the CCI reaching -200 level,
we want a divergence between the CCI and the

67
00:05:26,450 --> 00:05:31,840
price, but we also want a trend line break,
to confirm the switch in momentum.

68
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:36,870
Let’s see all the conditions met on the
Netflix stock.

69
00:05:36,870 --> 00:05:42,620
First, the CCI reaching oversold condition
twice.

70
00:05:42,620 --> 00:05:44,900
Then we see the regular divergence.

71
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:50,620
After that, we simply wait for a trend line
breakout.

72
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:59,120
After the price consolidated above the trend
line, we can safely enter long on the market.

73
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:02,789
The same pattern on Walt Disney stock.

74
00:06:02,789 --> 00:06:11,909
The stock price reached oversold levels twice,
the CCI indicator formed a divergence followed

75
00:06:11,909 --> 00:06:15,889
by a trend line breakout.

76
00:06:15,889 --> 00:06:22,219
As you can see, we did experienced some heat,
because the price consolidated for a while

77
00:06:22,219 --> 00:06:26,310
and retested the previous low, before it finally
took off.

78
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:33,150
So, don’t expect a sweet ride all the time,
we just have to put out stop orders accordingly

79
00:06:33,150 --> 00:06:36,220
and follow our initial plan.

80
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:39,490
Here is the IBM stock.

81
00:06:39,490 --> 00:06:49,759
Here’s the -200 level hit twice, the divergence
and the trend line breakout.

82
00:06:49,759 --> 00:06:57,029
Don’t be afraid to enter the market when
you see the CCI reaching overbought conditions

83
00:06:57,029 --> 00:07:01,889
because this is a classic beginner mistake.

84
00:07:01,889 --> 00:07:05,349
Another great trade on the visa stock.

85
00:07:05,349 --> 00:07:10,490
By now, i hope you trained your eyes to spot
for this CCI pattern.

86
00:07:10,490 --> 00:07:18,660
The oversold level hit twice, the regular
divergence and also the trend line break.

87
00:07:18,660 --> 00:07:22,520
You might wonder why we have to wait for the
breakout to enter the market.

88
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:29,659
In this example, if we could have entered
way sooner and obtained bigger profits.

89
00:07:29,659 --> 00:07:35,360
But you see, this was a fortunate case, many
times the market decides to search for lower

90
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:40,490
lows and go for the third time in oversold
area.

91
00:07:40,490 --> 00:07:45,870
By waiting for the trend line breakout, we
protect our capital and increase our chances

92
00:07:45,870 --> 00:07:49,080
for a true momentum shift.

93
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:53,029
Look at this example, on the Procter&Gamble
stock.

94
00:07:53,029 --> 00:07:59,650
Here we have our first 2 conditions met, but
we didn’t have the trend line breakout,

95
00:07:59,650 --> 00:08:02,750
so this was a no go trade.

96
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:10,559
Here, we have all conditions met and we have
a valid breakout.

97
00:08:10,559 --> 00:08:16,400
But as you can observe on the chart, the market
turned against our position and we lost this

98
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:18,070
trade.

99
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:23,139
But even if we lost the trade, this stock
still had potential for a good trade.

100
00:08:23,139 --> 00:08:32,620
Which came few weeks later, when we saw the
oversold level once again, the divergence

101
00:08:32,620 --> 00:08:35,209
and another trend line break.

102
00:08:35,209 --> 00:08:43,010
This time, the stock took off and we managed
to recoup our losses for the previous trade

103
00:08:43,010 --> 00:08:46,910
and recorded some extra profit.

104
00:08:46,910 --> 00:08:52,320
Like i said before, if you want to trade stocks
and increase your chances when you use this

105
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:57,500
strategy, a stock screener is one of the most
important tools in your arsenal.

106
00:08:57,500 --> 00:09:03,500
It will help you sort through thousands of
stocks to find only those that match specific

107
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:05,070
criteria.

108
00:09:05,070 --> 00:09:10,230
This way, you get to choose between stocks
and trade only the signals that have the greatest

109
00:09:10,230 --> 00:09:11,529
potential.

110
00:09:11,529 --> 00:09:17,730
This strategy is designed for timeframes higher
than 4 hours charts and for stock market,

111
00:09:17,730 --> 00:09:23,950
but I’ve also recorded good results on forex
market also, on lower timeframes.

112
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:28,139
If you got any value from this, please consider
subscribing to our channel, share and like

113
00:09:28,139 --> 00:09:32,340
